## Load packages
library(gdsfmt)

## Make ".gds" file
vcf.fn <- "../data/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.vcf"
snpgdsVCF2GDS(vcf.fn, "../outputs/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.gds", method="biallelic.only", verbose = TRUE)
## VCF Format --> SNP GDS Format
## Method: exacting biallelic SNPs
## Number of samples: 89
## Parsing "../data/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.vcf" ...
##  import 1785 variants.
## + genotype   { Bit2 89x1785 } *
## Optimize the access efficiency ...
## Clean up the fragments of GDS file:
##  open the file "../outputs/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.gds" (size: 53716).
##  # of fragments in total: 46.
##  save it to "../outputs/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.gds.tmp".
##  rename "../outputs/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.gds.tmp" (size: 53404).
##  # of fragments in total: 20.
snpgdsSummary("../outputs/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.gds")
## The file name: /Users/geyev15/Dropbox/TESIS_OZONO_ORGANIZADO/GENOMICS/outputs/89ind_maxmiss0.9_maf0.05.recode.gds 
## The total number of samples: 89 
## The total number of SNPs: 1785
